        "details": {
            "description": "<p>An obscuring fog covers the entirety of the hallway and northern room of the manor's second floor. Anyone moving through the area is subjected to an attack from a ghostly assailant.</p>",
            "disable": "<p>@Check[type:acrobatics|dc:23|name:Maneuver Through the Fog|traits:complex,haunt] to maneuver through the fog, @Check[type:religion|dc:21|name:Ward Off the Spirit|traits:complex,haunt] to ward off the spirit, or @Check[type:stealth|dc:23|name:Move Through the Fog Without Attracting Attention|traits:complex,haunt] to move through the fog without attracting attention. Disabling the haunt requires two successful checks, and each attempt takes two actions.</p>",
            "isComplex": true,
            "level": {
                "value": 5
            },
            "reset": "<p>The haunt lasts until disabled. It re-forms after 1 hour unless Eloise's ghost is put to permanent rest.</p>",
            "routine": "<p>(2 actions) The haunt uses an action to manifest an illusory shadow beside a creature ending its move in the fog, then attempts a spectral touch Strike against that creature. The shadow disappears after the Strike.</p>",
            "source": {
                "author": "",
                "value": "Pathfinder Society Scenario #3-02: The East Hill Haunting"
            }
